# Drag-and-Drop Transcriber + Prompted Summaries

A simple desktop-friendly app that lets you **drag & drop audio/video files**, transcribes them locally, and (optionally) generates **prompted summaries** in different styles (low/medium/high polish, email-ready, etc.).

## Features
- Drag & drop one or multiple files (WAV/MP3/MP4, etc.).
- Local transcription (Whisper/whisper.cpp or your chosen backend).
- One-click **summary modes**:
  - **Low**: light cleanup, keep your voice.
  - **Medium**: clarify, tighten, reorder slightly.
  - **High**: full editorial pass.
  - **Email**: “Hey {Name}, …” body + sign-off (Justin).
- Copy-to-clipboard and export to `.txt/.md`.
- Optional auto-copy to clipboard and model selection.

## Quick Start
```bash
# 1) Create and activate a virtual environment
python -m venv .venv
# Windows:
.venv\Scripts\activate
# macOS/Linux:
# source .venv/bin/activate

# 2) Install deps
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 3) Run the app
python gui_transcribe.py
